column5: How was your trip this year?

Very good. they all are. Fishing much slower than usual but we were getting used to a new lake and the weather was all over the board. cold rainy etc. I did take a day trip to Cliff with ProV and caught my first ever lake trout. That was fun. We boated 3 of them and then casted for musky for a bit. Got a couple follows and he had one hit but no fish.
It was a tough week for learning the lake.but glad i could help a bit.

We were at Onaway last Friday in August thu Sept 9. Decent fishing and weather. There was a bear in camp that had to be taken care of. Is there a public launch on Cliff? I heard it wa a good bass lake.
